to the Cathedral Kitchen.</p>
<p><b>A WEEKLY TIP ON CARING FOR OUR COMMON HOME</b>.
During chilly winter months wear an extra layer (or
two!) around the house and lower the setting on your
thermostat. This can preserve resources, reduce waste
emissions and save money. Installing a programmable
thermostat will allow you to automatically reduce
heating at night or at times when no one is home.</p>
<p><b>PARISH REMEMBRANCE</b>: <i>Throughout the year, because we
are the Cathedral Church, we remember in prayer at Mass
and Vespers each of the parishes and missions of the
Archdiocese of Seattle on a Sunday near their feast day</i>. This
week we pray for the parishes of St. Andrew in Sumner, St.
Francis Xavier in Toledo, and St. Barbara in Black Diamond.</p>

